eira%22+%22massaud+moises%22+%22tasso+da+silveira%22&hl=pt-BR&sa=X&ei=p4T5TuCSHYm2twfDgp3TAw&ved=0CD0Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q&f=false MOIS\u00c9S, Massaud.''History of Brazilian Literature: Modernism''. 6th Ed. S\u00e3o Paulo: Cultrix, 2001.] Retrieved on 27 December 2011.</ref>\n\n===Aviation===\n* [[Pierre Clostermann]] \u2013 World War II French pilot, engineer\n* [[Egon Albrecht]] \u2013 World War II German flying ace\n\n===Science===\n* [[Alex Kipman]] \u2013 scientist\n* [[C\u00e9sar Lattes]] \u2013 [[physicist]]\n* [[Ned Kock]] \u2013 [[information systems|systems]] scientist\n* [[Newton da Costa]] \u2013 [[mathematician]]\n* [[Ricardo Ramina]] \u2013 physician\n\n===Sports===\n; Football\n* [[Alexandro de Souza]]\n* [[Adriano Correia]]\n* [[Paulo Rink]]\n* [[Thiago Cionek]]\n* Fabiano, the Fabigoal\n\n; Mixed martial arts\n* [[Cristiane Justino|Cristiane \"Cyborg\" Justino]]\n* [[Mauricio \"Shogun\" Rua]]\n* [[Murilo Rua|Murilo \"Ninja\" Rua]]\n* [[Wanderlei Silva]]\n* [[Anderson Silva]]\n; Motorsports\n* [[Augusto Farfus]] \u2013 [[Deutsche Tourenwagen Masters|DTM]] driver for [[BMW]]\n* [[Enrique Bernoldi]] \u2013 [[Formula One]] driver \u2013 [[IndyCar Series|IndyCar]] driver\n* [[Raul Boesel]] \u2013 Formula One driver, [[IndyCar Series|IndyCar]] driver, [[1987 World Sportscar Championship season|1987]] [[World Sportscar Championship]] champion\n* [[Ricardo Zonta]] \u2013 Formula One driver, [[1998 FIA GT Championship season|1998]] [[FIA GT Championship]] champion\n\n; Basketball\n* [[Rolando Ferreira]] \u2013 (Gold medalist at the [[1987 Pan American Games]]), former [[Portland Trail Blazers]] player\n; Beach Volleyball\n* [[Emanuel Rego]] (Gold medalist in [[2004 Olympics]], Bronze in [[2008 Olympics]] and Silver in [[2012 Olympics]])\n* [[Agatha Bednarczuk]] (Silver medalist in [[2016 Olympics]])\n; Horse Racing\n* [[Jo\u00e3o Moreira (jockey)|Jo\u00e3o Moreira]] \u2013 Jockey\n; Poker\n* [[Alexandre Gomes]] (WSOP and WPT world champion 2008\u20132009)\n\n